<DOCNO> AP890519-0070 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
a government scientist says his detailed new 
analysis disproves the theory that volcanoes are more likely to 
erupt at certain times of the year 
historically volcanoes have erupted slightly more often in some 
months than others leading to disputes over whether the variation 
was enough to constitute a periodic pattern 
richard b stothers concluded that it isnt in a report in the 
may issue of geophysical research letters published by the 
american geophysical union 
stothers of the national aeronautics and space administrations 
goddard space flight center in greenbelt md compared the dates 
of recorded strong volcanic eruptions between 1500 and 1980 
during that time 265 eruptions were recorded in the first half 
of each calendar year and 236 in the last six months a difference 
stothers said is not statistically significant 
breaking down the eruptions by month and area stothers did find 
some clustering but this was explainable he concluded 
for example nearly all eruptions south of 50 degrees south 
latitude occurred between november and april 
this is almost certainly because that is summer in that part of 
the world the time of year the nearly uninhabited region is most 
often visited by outsiders who would record eruptions stothers 
said 
no similar pattern was seen in the far north where residents 
are always present to notice eruptions 
stothers monthly analysis found a peak average of 52 eruptions 
in february between the years 1500 and 1980 and a minimum of 36 
eruptions in the months of april and december during that period 
the average number of eruptions in other months fell in between 
those two a variation within the range that statisticians would 
expect to occur in a random sample 
stothers analysis rebuts several studies done in the late 1800s 
and early in this century that indicated a seasonality to volcanic 
eruptions 
at least one 1917 report speculated that eruptions would cluster 
around the equinoxes in the spring and fall as a result of changes 
in the angle of the sun 
periodic springtime eruptions of some volcanoes have been 
associated with melting snow seeping into the ground and reacting 
with molton lava below the ground scientists have suggested 
but seasonality occurring at individual volcanoes disappears 
when they are averaged in with many others around the world 
according to stothers analysis 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP890519-0071 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the first black woman to sit on the 
pennsylvania supreme court has been stripped of her office and 
91000 salary by her colleagues because of her age 
the high court split 42 on thursday with chief justice robert 
nc nix registering what he called a most vociferous dissent 
justice juanita kidd stout was forced off the bench retroactive 
to her 70th birthday on march 6 she had not participated in any 
new cases since then the state constitution requires judges to 
retire at 70 but stouts attorney argued she was exempt because 
she was appointed not elected 
justice nicholas papadakos writing for the majority said 
appointed judges should not be exempt 
we do not believe that the equal protection clause of the 
federal constitution confers any greater rights upon appointed 
judges than upon elected or retained judges papadakos said in 
agreeing with state attorney general ernest preate jr who brought 
the lawsuit 
there is no question that justice stout is widely recognized 
as an outstanding judge and justice preate said the position 
that i argued is simply that the constitution must apply to 
everyone including supreme court justices 
gov robert p casey appointed stout in february 1988 to fill a 
vacancy expected to last only a year her term was extended when 
the court canceled judicial elections in 1988 on a technicality 
the court then ordered casey to extend her appointment to jan 
2 1990 but did not address the age question 
nix who shared his office with stout said the majoritys 
opinion would hurt the judicial system 
many highly qualified former judges who have surpassed the age 
of 70 are by the majoritys decision prevented from filling 
vacancies in our court system on an interim basis he said 
if there is a sadness to todays decision it is that this 
court which traces its existence back to 1681 has only had two 
female justices both of whom assumed office by appointments to 
fill a vacancy 
nix held out the hope that stout could become the first person 
appointed as a senior justice a retired judge who continues to 
work to ease court backlogs to the supreme court 
