iran has filed suit against the 
united states in the world court over the loss of 290 lives in the 
downing of an iranian jetliner last year a court official said 
today 
tehran has asked the court to rule that the united states is 
responsible to pay compensation to the islamic republic to the 
amount to be determined by the court for the injuries suffered 
by the islamic republic and the bereaved families the official 
quoted irans submission to the court 
iran filed its application at the court on wednesday said the 
official who spoke on condition of anonymity in line with court 
practice 
it was not clear whether the bush administration was planning to 
take part in the proceedings the us embassy in the hague 
declined comment 
the case involves the downing of an iranian airbus jet by the 
uss vincennes on july 3 1988 all 290 passengers and crew of the 
plane died in the incident which occurred after the airbus was 
erroneously identified as an iranian fighter plane by the 
vincennes crew 
president reagan said at the time that the families of the 
victims would be compensated as an expression of grief but that 
no other reparations would be made the former administration said 
the unspecified compensation would go to families and not the 
government of iran 
but recently bush administration officials said they cannot 
compensate the families until their receive more information from 
iran about the victims 
the world court officially known as the international court of 
justice is the judicial branch of the united nations it has no 
enforcement powers and depends on voluntary adherence to its 
rulings 
in documents filed at the courts registry iran also asked the 
court to quash a march 17 decision by the international civil 
aviation organization which deplored the incident but did not 
blame the us government the court official told the associated 
press 
the court is considering when to begin proceedings in the case 
which pits the united states against iran in the world court for 
the second time since 1979 
in that year the carter administration filed suit against iran 
over the fate of 55 american diplomats held hostage at the us 
embassy in tehran the court ruled in favor of the us government 
ordering iran to immediately release the hostages 
the iranian government ignored the court ruling but later freed 
the hostages in january 1980 after an elaborate deal was reached 
with washington 
the united states withdrew from proceedings in the other major 
world court case in which it was involved earlier in the decade in 
1984 nicaragua sought a halt to us support for the contra rebels 
and the court sided with the leftist sandinista government two 
years later 
only days before that complaint was filed the reagan 
administration canceled its acceptance of world court jurisdiction 
in central american affairs 
of the more than 150 un member nations only 49 have accepted 
the courts authority as compulsory in settling conflicts between 
states the united states is one of them with the exception of 
central american disputes 
