chengs coffin was taken on a twohour funeral procession 
through taipei streets by 2000 supporters before the memorial 
service outside the presidential office building the crowd later 
swelled to nearly 10000 people 
riot police erected barbedwire barricades outside the 
presidential office building to prevent the mourners from getting 
too close to the building 
police said the procession was illegal because demonstrations 
are not permitted in the vicinity of th presidential office 
building 
after chans selfimmolation a protestant priest kao 
chunming led the crowd in singing hymns and a taiwanese folk song 
we are all native taiwanese the crowd also shouted slogans 
of taiwan needs independence 
the mourners included chen wanchen a dissident taiwan 
journalist who has lived in exile in the united states for 10 years 
and who has been banned from returning because she has advocated an 
independent taiwan dissidents said she slipped back into the 
country last week from the phillipines 
opposition legislator hsu jongshu said both cheng and chan had 
died for press freedom and political liberalization and she 
promised to campaign to achieve their objectives 
the nationalists who fled to taiwan in 1949 after losing a 
civil war in china continue to maintain they are the legitimate 
government of all china and that taiwan is a chinese province 
taiwan and china are opposed to an independent taiwan and china 
indicated it would use force to prevent the establishment of an 
independent taiwan 
