month at age 77 and had planned to visit jamestown for the first 
time in more than 30 years on friday to get a key to the city and 
give the festival a sendoff officials said 
five giant photographs of lucy adorned city hall and a high 
school band played her television theme song as carlson announced 
the creation of the festival 
carlson said the festival would commission up to three plays per 
year and arrange for them to be premiered at jamestowns reg lenna 
civic center 
this memorial to lucy unlike a building bearing her name has 
a future as lively as she was said carlson just as she was on 
the cutting edge of comedy for her time this festival is going to 
keep on breaking new comedy ground 
organizers hope to establish a repertory company to perform the 
plays and to hold the first festival sometime next year 
carlson said miss ball and her husband gary morton had 
reviewed plans for the festival and were excited about the project 
miss ball died of a ruptured aorta april 26 while recovering 
from earlier emergency heart surgery 
she was born aug 6 1911 in jamestown about 60 miles south of 
buffalo and grew up in nearby celoron she went on to star in 
movies and the television series i love lucy 
although miss ball had not visited the community since 1956 she 
kept in touch with childhood friends and supported local causes 
