shamir to president bush asking the united states to spearhead an 
international campaign to raise an estimated 2 billion to provide 
new housing education and jobs for the palestinian refugees 
israel has also raised the refugee rehabilitation proposal with 
japan and arens will ask the european economic community for its 
help when he meets with the group in brussels next week he said 
oilrich arab states which in the past have refused to provide 
financing for such projects could also take part if they want he 
added 
arens said he views the rehabilitation plan as a concrete 
response to the frustrations that spawned an 18month palestinian 
uprising in which almost 500 palestinians have been killed 
the proposed elections would let palestinians elect 
representatives who would negotiate with the israelis for selfrule 
but the proposal does not answer some of the question which the 
arabs view as most pressing such as whether the plo will be given 
a role in elections and whether international supervision will be 
allowed 
