the arab league to work out a settlement leaving aoun in charge in 
the 310squaremile enclave north and east of beirut where most of 
lebanons christians live 
repeated efforts by the arab league to implement a truce it 
called april 28 have failed mainly because the syrians and druse 
continue shelling the christian coastline to keep aoun from 
receiving supplies by sea 
