service from nashville to paris 
wyche fowler dga was reimbursed by nongovernment interests 
for trips to cuba san francisco and fayetteville ark 
not everything senators touched turned to gold last year 
freshman herbert kohl a multimillionaire did well with his bakery 
stock but his milwaukee bucks national basketball association 
franchise lost 95000 although it generated revenues of 121 
million 
in most cases it is next to impossible to tell a senators 
financial condition from the disclosure statements items of 
income assets and liabilities are listed in broad brackets thus 
6000 interest earned shows up with a value of 5001 to 15000 
a 10 million gain from a property sale would be listed only as 
worth 250001 and up 
some of the wealthiest senators have assets in trusts so the 
statement of edward m kennedy dmass gives no clue that he has 
an interest in trusts worth tens of millions of dollars he has no 
liabilities 
similarly the extensive wealth of jay rockefeller dwva is 
tied up in trusts 
when trusts are excluded kohl could be the richest senator 
with assets of up to nearly 28 million and liabilities of less 
than 2 million john c danforth rmo whose grandfather founded 
ralston purina lists assets of up to 13 million and no 
liabilities 
john heinz rpa whose family started and still owns a large 
block of hj heinz co the ketchupandpickle giant reported 
assets of at least 112 million and perhaps 136 million with 
liabilities of about 1 million 
nancy l kassebaum rkan who owns real estate and a wichita 
radio station listed assets of up to 4 million with maximum 
liabilities of under 15 million 
