bigmoney politics because the power balance among them is 
determined largely by their financial strength 
in a scandal that began last summer and has reached the top of 
politics and business the recruit co is accused of of trying to 
buy favors with large donations and insider stock deals that 
benefited about 160 politicians bureaucrats and business 
executives 
gotoda described the reform plan to reporters as 
forwardlooking and said the most important thing is how to 
implement it 
similar scandals have been repeated every 10 years or so and 
this proposal is also intended to eliminate the root of such 
scandals he said 
the reforms now go to the parliament as legislation and are 
expected to be enacted by november 
provisaions include a ban on speculating with political funds 
requiring that the funds be in government bonds or deposited in 
banks a ban on fundraising parties by cabinet members which are 
a common way to dodge limits on political donations and reducing 
the need for campaign money by gradually lowering the number of 
parliament seats from 512 to 471 
