1972 under which naturally caused forest fires were allowed to burn 
unless they threatened lives or structures 
yellowstone spokeswoman joan anzelmo confirmed friday that 
lightningcaused fires will be fought in the park this summer 
agee said fire management policies in the future will have to be 
based on the ecosystem concept applying policies to areas in a 
region with similar ecologies 
we can no longer rely on the myth of natural regulation 
said the chairman of the university of washingtons division of 
forest resource management these are not closed systems 
changes in the worlds climate also will have to be considered 
agee said and current policies are not sufficient to the task 
