pipeline service cos marine manager 
an investigator asked schier how much oil would had been removed 
from prince william sound if the loaded barge had been docked at 
bligh reef when the ship ran aground march 24 spilling 109 
million gallons of crude oil 
i cant respond to that he said 
on thursday alaskas environmental commissioner said the exxon 
valdez disaster proved the oil industry couldnt fulfill its 
promise to contain and remove a massive oil spill quickly in prince 
william sound 
but an exxon corp executive told federal investigators that it 
